(secondQuint)Efficacy and Safety of Dexlansoprazole MR and Lansoprazole on Healing of Erosive Esophagitis.

 This is a Phase 3, randomized, double-blind, multi-center, active-controlled, 3-arm study with an 8 week treatment period.

 This study will compare the efficacy of Dexlansoprazole MR (60 mg and 90 mg) with that of Lansoprazole (30 mg) when administered orally as a single daily dose in the morning, before breakfast.

 The study is designed to evaluate healing of erosive esophagitis and the effect of the therapy on relieving gastroesophageal reflux disease related symptoms.

 The study consists of two periods, a screening period (maximum 21 days) and a treatment period, which will last up to 8 weeks.

